- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on event-based media retrieval and summarization.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper deals with social media platforms and user-generated content.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as natural language processing techniques are often used in event detection and summarization.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with multimedia content on social media platforms.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the development of software tools or systems for event detection and retrieval on social media.
